Citrus latifolia

   [4631.jpg]
   Authority Tan.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Rutaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names Tahiti lime, Persian lime, bearss lime, Persische Limette,
   Tahitilimette, lima da Persia
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 4631

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Hackett C 1982 pp 101 [FER, PHO, DEP, PH, TEXT, TEMP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial evergreen tree. The tree is 'everbearing', some bloom and
   fruit maturation occurs in every month of the year.
   COMMON NAMES
   Tahiti lime, Limon Limon persa, Limon persico.
   FURTHER INF
   The oil from the rind or the leaves may cause dermatitis upon contact
   with the skin of some people. (See also under Citrus ssp.)

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
